{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86530909-b14e-472e-9c3e-79ff2f5b79ce","content":"Three files to update:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Update NuGet packages — run `dotnet outdated` (or manually bump any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` / `Microsoft.Extensions.*` references to their **11.x** versions).\n- Run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify.\n- Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/migration) for any breaking API changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ddf634fb-a37c-4a18-87eb-822f2532eb99","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the relevant files.\n\nHere's what needs to change:\n\n1. **`.csproj`** — Change `<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>` to `<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>`\n2. **`global.json`** — Change SDK version from `10.0.100` to `11.0.100`\n\n\n3. **`Dockerfile`** — Update the base images from `aspnet:10.0` and `sdk:10.0` to their 11.0 equivalents\n\nI should also mention updating NuGet packages to their 11.x versions and checking the migration guide for any breaking changes.","outputTokens":500},"id":"433f22e0-cabb-42c9-84b1-b2d67a63ea4c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:58:09.376Z","parentId":"bdfdea24-efe3-42e2-904b-989c1bbd6b94"}
